-- British-American Declines to 1-Month Low on Profit Forecast
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2012-01-16T12:48:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/british-american-declines-to-1-month-low-on-profit-drop-forecast.html
British-American Investments Co. (BRIT) ,
the Kenyan financial services group that began trading its
shares in September, declined to the lowest in a month after
saying last week annual profit would fall at least 25 percent.  Shares (BRIT)  in the company dropped as much as 4.4 percent to
4.40 shillings before closing down 2.2 percent at 4.50 shillings
as of 3 p.m. in the capital, Nairobi, the lowest level since
Dec. 15.  “The profit warning is still weighing heavily on
investors,” Eric Musau, a research analyst at Nairobi-based
Standard Investment Bank Ltd., said by phone today.  The shares have only risen during two trading sessions this
year, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
